Greetings. I am an atma fabricant--or, to the layman, one who fabricates atma. I can synthesize atma from the memories of adventure stored deep within your body and soul. If you have need of my services, you need only speak the word.<Prompt>
Ask for something. <Selection Dialog>No thanks. Synthetic atma. My memories. Show me the atma.<Prompt>
As you are no doubt aware, the substance we call atma is a crystalline agglomeration of soul energy that can be harvested from the bodies of fallen Abyssean fiends.<Prompt>
The abundant power that it imbues when infused into our bodies is not in question. The perilous means by which it must be acquired, however, leaves something to be desired.<Prompt>

After all, bolstering the strength of one man means little if ten others must lose their lives in the process. Thus was the impetus behind our research: to discover a means for extracting atma from resources at our immediate disposal.<Prompt>
We experimented with nearly every substance in sight--be it animal, vegetable, or mineral. Yet each time, the atma produced was small, fragile, and entirely absent of the power we sought.<Prompt>

Then, one day, we hit upon the obvious answer that we had so long overlooked...ourselves. Yes, the atma extracted from our own bodies--particularly those richly possessed of experiences and memories--these housed a power rivalling that harvested from the most vicious of fiends.<Prompt>
If you possess such memories, then I can bring forth the latent power that resides within you as well.<Prompt>
Fear not, for there is everything to gain and nothing to lose. Save for some cruor, that is...<Prompt>
Curious, is it not. That potent physical energy can be extracted from such a tenuous, intangible thing...<Prompt>
But the strength our memories and experiences give us is real, if all too easily overlooked. Once isolated, it is simply a matter of recalling it, solidifying it, and bringing it to the fore.<Prompt>
Surely you understand of what it is I speak, yes. Your greatest accomplishments--those that make others stand in wonderment and admiration when you they hear your name.<Prompt>

We summon forth the energies from the deepest recesses of your psyche, and infuse it into the cruor you carry. The resultant agglomeration of organic mineral and soul energy is synthetic atma.<Prompt>

Mind you, the deeper and more puissant your energies, the more cruor will be necessary to contain it all. If you wish to have me assay the powers that lie dormant within you, simply speak the word.<Prompt>
Very well. We shall see what latent powers you possess. Stand still and clear your mind...<Prompt>
Yes...it is as I thought... Long and far have you traveled...many a battle have you fought...<Prompt>
Yes, I see within you <Numeric (Parameter 0)> <Singular/Plural Choice (Parameter 0)>[memory/memories] that I could process into atma. Which shall I extract.<Prompt>
...And yet, I see nothing tangible enough for me to process. I am sorry.<Prompt>

I'm a Resistance officer charged with overseeing the Dominion effort, and we're looking for a few good <Prompt>.[men/women]. Since I don't see any around, it looks like you'll have to do.<Prompt>
Ask about something. <Selection Dialog>Not now. General information. State of the Resistance. State of the enemy. Exchange Dominion Notes. Exchange battle trophies.<Prompt>
Ask about something. <Selection Dialog>Not now. The Dominion effort.... How do I do my part. What's in it for me.<Prompt>
Wake up, soldier! I don't know if you're blind or stupid, but if you haven't noticed, there's a war going on around you.<Prompt>

The Resistance is locked in a bitter struggle to take back our rightful land from the hordes, and secure a future for our kind. We call this the Dominion effort. Has an inspiring ring to it, doesn't it, soldier.<Prompt>

And if you haven't noticed, we don't exactly have a surplus of personnel. Hell, I just got a field promotion from sergeant to tactician when my predecessor got his head lopped clean off by a fiend. Now they've got some sissy boy doing my old job, but do you hear me complainin'.<Prompt>
Anyhow, if you've got half a bloody stump of a leg to stand on and an arm to carry a blade, consider yourself recruited. Now listen up, soldier, because I'm only going to say this once.<Prompt>
I'll put this in terms even a dullard like you can understand. The enemy we face consists of two types of fiends: nasty ones, and even nastier ones.<Prompt>
We've got legions of ugly monsters prowling the land in throngs. We cut them down, and lure their even nastier buddies out of hiding.<Prompt>
These fiends are the beating heart of our enemy. Bring them down, and our battle is as good as won. Get it. Good. Now hop to it, soldier!<Prompt>
Hah! Ya may be short on wits, but you've got pluck. There may be hope for you yet, soldier.<Prompt>

If you're ready to make yourself useful, then you'll want to seek out one of our outposts. There's three in the area, so even a rookie like yourself should be able to stumble upon one of 'em by dumb luck.<Prompt>
Talk with a sergeant there, and sign up for one of our operations--Dominion Ops, we call 'em for short. Each op will involve exterminating a prescribed quota of a particular variety of fiend.<Prompt>

If you're halfway competent at your job, the Resistance will gradually expand its sphere of influence over the hordes. Our ultimate goal is complete domination against all manner of fiends. That's one hundred percent, soldier!<Prompt>
What if I just kill fiends without signing up for ops,  you say. Don't give me any of that lip, soldier!<Prompt>

Listen. Every fiend you bring down will aid the cause. But we can't be certain that we've achieved complete domination unless you sign up for ops, and report your success to the sergeant. You'll also be rewarded for your efforts. Bet that got your interest quick, didn't it.<Prompt>
There's more, soldier. This may sound bloody obvious--well, maybe not to a lackwit like you--but success in your efforts will raise the spirits of our entire company.<Prompt>

With the resulting boost in morale, our troops will fight with even greater fervor, affording us all manner of advantages in battle.  What kind of advantages.  Hah! That's for us to know and you to find out, soldier!<Prompt>
Expand our sphere of influence over the peons, and we'll start to lure the big boys out of the woodwork.<Prompt>
Take them out, and the biggest, baddest foes will start to show up. Where does it all end, you say. It doesn't! This is war, soldier, not a Lightsday afternoon walk in the park!<Prompt>
Now, where was I. The enemy leaders pack a punch, but they rely on their flunkies as the foundation for their strength.<Prompt>

Cut their subordinates out from underneath them, and they won't have a leg--or gnarled, twisted appendage--to stand upon. That's smart fighting. And in war, you fight smart or you die, soldier!<Prompt>
I couldn't tell you how many of these buggers we're up against, but I do know this. Each one we kill brings us closer to our goal of utter domination.<Prompt>
To keep morale high, we can't let up the attack on the enemy leaders. You got all that, soldier.<Prompt>
What's in it for you. You've got some nerve, soldier!<Prompt>
You're here to follow orders, not question them! When I say  jump,  you say  how many malms high, sir!.  Are we understood, soldier!.<Prompt>

When you report back after completing an operation or successfully bring down a notorious foe, you'll be awarded remuneration in the form of something we call Dominion Notes.<Prompt>

These notes can be exchanged for supplies to serve you on the field of battle: equipment, medicine, and more. And we're not talking your run-of-the-mill items here. This is some impressive stuff. I daresay it's worth more than your life, soldier.<Prompt>

Bet that put a spark in your eyes, didn't it. What's more, bring back battle trophies--the severed heads and gore-stained limbs of the fiends you slay--and we will reward your accomplishments with guerdon.<Prompt>
There are five echelons of trophies in total. Slaying more powerful fiends will yield more prestigious trophies, which in turn will earn you more valuable guerdon.<Prompt>

Battle trophies can even be exchanged for each other. Multiple lower-echelon trophies can be upgraded to a single trophy of a higher echelon, or vice versa. If you've got half a brain inside that skull of yours, you'll take advantage of this to obtain the guerdon you desire.<Prompt>

Dominion Ops is the name given to Resistance operations whose objective is the suppression of the monster population.<Prompt>
Besides the detachment encamped here, two others can be found operating in the area. If you wish to partake in Dominion Ops, you may do so by speaking with either me or a fellow sergeant.<Prompt>
Likewise, you may report back to any one of us upon the successful completion of your objective, at which time you will be issued your reward for assistance rendered.<Prompt>
As long as he or she is in the same area, any sergeant is authorized to attend to your needs. Keep this in mind, and you won't waste precious time hopping between encampments.<Prompt>
Each Dominion Ops successfully completed slightly expands our sphere of influence over the Abyssean hordes.<Prompt>
Needless to say, our ultimate goal is complete and utter domination. Every individual effort counts!<Prompt>
Bear in mind, however, that the enemy will not be taking any of this sitting down. Do not be surprised if an especially fearsome fiend emerges in an attempt to thwart our efforts.<Prompt>
And unfortunately for us, the Abyssean fiends are confoundingly fertile. Their numbers will literally explode if left unchecked, in turn causing our hard-won sphere of influence to diminish.<Prompt>

As the sphere of influence directly influences troop morale, it is imperative that we do not slacken our efforts. We earnestly ask for your cooperation in keeping the area safe for all survivors.<Prompt>
To cancel an objective in progress, you must seek out one of the sergeants in the area.<Prompt>

The same applies if you wish to review your progress or report your success. In the case of the latter, you will also be issued your reward, which includes Dominion Notes, for assistance rendered.<Prompt>
